  "prompt": "How does one make the best omelette?",
  "response": "To make the best omelette, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ingredients:\n- Fresh eggs\n- Salt and pepper\n- Butter or oil\n- Optional fillings (cheese, ham, vegetables)\n\n2. Preparation:\n- Whisk eggs until well blended\n- Season with salt and pepper\n- Prepare fillings in advance\n\n3. Cooking technique:\n- Use a non-stick pan\n- Heat pan on medium-low\n- Add butter or oil\n- Pour whisked eggs into the pan\n- Let eggs set slightly\n- Use spatula to gently lift edges\n- When eggs are mostly set, add fillings to one side\n- Fold omelette in half\n- Cook until golden and filling is warm\n\n4. Pro tips:\n- Use room temperature eggs\n- Don't overbeat eggs\n- Don't overcook (eggs should be slightly creamy)\n- Use fresh ingredients\n- Experiment with different fillings\n\n5. Variations:\n- French-style (softer, less cooked)\n- American-style (firmer, more cooked)\n- Add herbs like chives or parsley\n- Try different cheese types\n\nPractice and personal preference will help you perfect your technique.",
